Package org.treetank.service.xml.xpath.axis

Class Summary
ExceptAxis ExceptAxis Returns the nodes of the first operand except those of the second operand.
ForAxis ForAxis IAxis that handles a for expression.
IfAxis IfAxis IAxis that represents the conditional expression based on the keywords if, then, and else.
IntersectAxis IntersectAxis Returns an intersection of two operands.
RangeAxis RangeExpr A range expression can be used to construct a sequence of consecutive integers.
SequenceAxis SequenceAxis Axis that represents a sequence of singleExpressions, normally separated by a ','.
UnionAxis UnionAxis Returns an union of two operands.
VariableAxis VariableAxis Evaluated the given binding sequence, the variable is bound to and stores in a list that can be accessed by other sequences and notifies its observers, as soon as a new value of the binding sequence has been evaluated.
